timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Kei time! Kamara gives @ColumbusCrew the lead over @SoundersFC. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Inside MLS
timelineItems.text: GOAL: Columbus Crew SC 1 (Kamara, 10') - Seattle Sounders 0 #CLBvSEA #MLS

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: Tamara just runs over Chad Marshall. Lackadaisical defending - it’s the theme for the day. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Raving Green Blog
timelineItems.text: Can't say that was against the run of play. The crew look great. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Nino Torres
timelineItems.text: What a difference from last week. #CrewSC is making crosses that matter, not rushing the services, they're aimimg for the target #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Kyle McCarthy
timelineItems.text: Crew SC started brightly and took advantage to grab the opener. Clever run by Kamara to meet Francis' tempting cross. #CLBvSEA #MLS

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: Pineda crosses towards Martins, deflected right to Clark. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.desc: Offside, Seattle Sounders FC. Gonzalo Pineda tries a through ball, but Obafemi Martins is caught offside.
timelineItems.title: OFFSIDE: Obafemi Martins chips it into the goal, but is caught too far up

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: Higuain to Kamara, who heads over. Dangerous again, and this match is open. Sounders clear resulting corner. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 15': Kamara with another header. Pipa delivers the cross and Kei's header is deflected for a corner. #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Tony Tchani (Columbus Crew SC) right footed shot from the center of the box is saved in the center of the goal.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Tony Tchani chips it from inside the box, but cannot get past Stefan Frei

timelineItems.name: Soccer Gods
timelineItems.text: Kei Kamara already has entirely too many goals for 2015. Here's one more. 1-0 #CLBvSEA https://t.co/6ZLbHBkHu5

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: Seattle puts one in, but it deflected off the, er, rump of an offside Martins. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: Everyone thinks Higuain is offside, but he crosses for Tchani who volleys right at Frei. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Seattle Sounders FC
timelineItems.text: Let's go! #CLBvSEA http://t.co/LX95dH9ynu

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: Pineda draws a foul in his own end. The whites are really sharp kits! #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Sounders Matchday
timelineItems.text: 1’ - On a scale of 1-Clooney…how studly do the Sounders look in those kits? #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: Crew wearing their home black tonight. #GottaSellThoseAwayJerseys #Adidas #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Justin Meram (Columbus Crew) shoots it from the left side of the box, but it is saved.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Stefan Frei leaps and stops a charging Justin Meram

timelineItems.desc: A pair of clubs which have gotten off to bright starts this season met when Columbus Crew SC played host to Seattle Sounders FC on Saturday evening at Mapfre Stadium.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: Columbus Crew SC vs. Seattle Sounders | May 9, 2015

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: Seattle needs to learn the difference between a good defense and just getting good results. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: Seattle leaving Pipa alone in the middle of the field on the counter and lots of space out wide. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 21': Higuain with a beautiful through-pass to Meram. His shot is blocked by Frei. Finlay's 2nd attempt goes over the bar! #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Columbus Crew SC 1, Seattle Sounders FC 1. Clint Dempsey (Seattle Sounders FC) left footed shot from outside the box to the bottom left corner of the goal.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Clint Dempsey curls a beauty past Steve Clark to tie the game up

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: Every time a #Sounders player thinks too much, #CrewSC pressures to regain possession. #CLBvSEA #MLS

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 24': Goal for the Sounders. Dempsey hits it home from distance. #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Sounders Nation
timelineItems.text: So. Seriously. Was @Stefan24Frei a hockey goalie in the past? Boy got skills. @SoundersFC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Hunter
timelineItems.text: Dempsey with a strike. Damn. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: DEMPSEY FROM DISTANCE!! #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Brooke Tunstall
timelineItems.text: Wow, sports are fun tonight! @clint_dempsey with a blast from about 23 yards. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: Dempsey catches the Crew defense...wait for it...watching. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Soccer Gods
timelineItems.text: Obafemi Martins has been getting all the press. Dempsey needed to show off. 1-1 #CLBvSEA https://t.co/APUjqFa8Mh

timelineItems.name: Columbus Wired
timelineItems.text: Steve Clark dives and smacks the ball out of reach of #Sounders attackers. Clark performing pretty well so far this match #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Raving Green Blog
timelineItems.text: Ross tells it like it is: "nice to see some life in this stadium." But I wanted him to say "fire" #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: Marshall gets there but Clark holds comfortably at the left post. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Centro Deportivo
timelineItems.text: 32' CK for the #Sounders. Marshall heads the incoming ball in, but Clark does well to hang onto it. #CLBvSEA #MLS

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: WATCH: The Nordecke erupts as @keikamara gives #CrewSC the lead! #CLBvSEA http://t.co/v44H75n1gD

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Excellent job closing that passing lane by Seattle, or it could've been 2-1. #CrewSC #Sounders

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: Alonso trips over the thick Columbus air and falls to the ground. #CLBvSEA #MLS

timelineItems.name: Mark Grainda
timelineItems.text: The Nordeke at full volume tonight, sounding great on TV #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Carly M Haas
timelineItems.text: These @SoundersFC are going to be covered in grass stains with all their flopping! #CrewSC GO CREW! http://t.co/Cxe6aErrq6

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Justin Meram (Columbus Crew SC) left footed shot from the center of the box is saved in the center of the goal.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Justin Meram boot from short distance ends up in the arms of Stefan Frei

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: I was about to comment on how Seattle were looking much more organized. Apparently I'm a preemptive jinx. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Eric Hole
timelineItems.text: This all counter soccer is making for a super exciting game #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Wide shot from Higuain, now in sole possession of 7th all time in #CrewSC history in that category, passing GBS.

timelineItems.name: John B.
timelineItems.text: A legitimate and well-executed tackle in which the attacking player falls over? FOUL wat #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.desc: Emanuel Pogatetz (Columbus Crew SC) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Emanuel Pogatetz is booked for colliding with Obafemi Martins

timelineItems.name: Greg Benson
timelineItems.text: Pogatetz discovers the little known "headers aren't allowed" rule in @MLS. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: Yellow for Pogatetz, who rammed into Martins on an aerial duel. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: Columbus had been playing the "how hard can we hit before we get a card" game, and they find out. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: This @Clint_Dempsey blast leaves it even-stevens between #CLBvSEA at half. WATCH: http://t.co/u1V3gVqS7S

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 45': That's it for the first half. We're tied here at @MAPFREStadium. #CrewSC #CLBvSEA http://t.co/vv3zmoUtqP

timelineItems.name: Erin Fox
timelineItems.text: Where Saturdays belong. #CrewSC #Nordecke http://t.co/JDh0Fd36d3

timelineItems.name: Inside MLS
timelineItems.text: HALFTIME: Columbus Crew SC 1 - Seattle Sounders 1 #CLBvSEA #MLS

timelineItems.text: #CLBvSEA knotted at HT, #DCvSKC looking tense, #VANvPHI looking comfy, #DALvLA just about to start. #INeedMoarScreens

timelineItems.text: The Black & Gold with 6 shots on target, compared to Seattle's 3. Catch all match stats here: http://t.co/4qiUhAN7uA #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.text: #CLBvSEA Go Sounders @SoundersFC 1-1 Halftime http://t.co/8sDAB5k7Df

timelineItems.text: Crew SC's 14 first half shots tonight was tied for the most in a first half this season. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.text: 46': We're kicked-off for the second half. Both teams have sent their starting 11 back on. #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Tom Biro
timelineItems.text: Zero: number of times Columbus "supporters" can talk about support in Seattle. #cleanyourownhouse #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: We’re back underway for the 2nd half. #CrewSC #Sounders

timelineItems.text: Second half... #CLBvSEA http://t.co/pU9kCC5RDQ

timelineItems.text: 73': Meram with a shot from the top of the box. Frei saves for a corner. #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Tchani goes down to the field after hopping around, apparently a foot/leg thing. Back up now though. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Radio Cascadia
timelineItems.text: Kamara Shor deflected by Evans for a corner. 4' #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Sounders Nation
timelineItems.text: Looks good seeing our boys sporting white. #CLBvSEA @SoundersFC

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Higuain's shot went through a channel consisting of five Sounders defenders. #CrewSC #Sounders

timelineItems.name: Guy Swiftie
timelineItems.text: Pipa makes it 2-1!!!! #CLBvSEA #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: TWC SportsChannel OH
timelineItems.text: Federico Higuain scores his 2nd goal of the season. Assist to Ethan Finlay in the 50th minute. #CrewSC leads 2-1.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 52': Kamara fires a shot. Frei puts his fists up to save the powerful strike! #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.text: GOAL: Columbus Crew SC 2 (Higuain, 50') - Seattle Sounders 1 #CLBvSEA #MLS

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC adds to its League-leading total with its sixth goal scored between the 46th and 60th minute intervals.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: Getting in the rhythm. The team's warming up for @SoundersFC. Less than 30 minutes to kick-off! #CrewSC #CLBvSEA http://t.co/xqeiAyL3WQ

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: Curious to see how the fans greet Marshall in his first game in Columbus since moving to Seattle. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.desc: Ethan Finlay (Columbus Crew SC) hits the bar with a left footed shot from the center of the box. Assisted by Federico Higuaín.
timelineItems.title: MISS: Ethan Finlay sends it just high in front of the goal

timelineItems.name: Alex Caulfield
timelineItems.text: Perfect night for it. #CLBvSEA http://t.co/G1O5BBFCGs

timelineItems.text: The teams warming up prior to kickoff. #CLBvSEA http://t.co/agacGwsrZY

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: 2 players on the field tonight won the MLS Cup in 2008 with #CrewSC. Both play for the #Sounders now (Marshall & Evans). #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: #CLBvSEA getting underway on MLS Live. Tune in right meow. http://t.co/TTvNHkwesk http://t.co/2svxkEz3yP

timelineItems.name: FÃºtbol MLS
timelineItems.text: Dos delanteras letales se miden a rivales en buen momento: http://t.co/x3dBIhRiIZ #CLBvSEA http://t.co/Yx7oyQ5Tb0

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: The teams are entering the pitch. Just a few moments away from kick-off. Let's do this! #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: 57’ Ethan Finlay with ANOTHER golden opportunity and he skies a shot over the bar after skinning Chad Marshall in the box. Woof. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: John Clem
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC should have four or five goals by now if we could finish a bit better.

timelineItems.name: Centro Deportivo
timelineItems.text: 58': GOAL! Kamara makes it 3-1 after a nice combination between Meram and JImenez. #CLBvSEA #MLS

timelineItems.name: Kevin Parks
timelineItems.text: So much stupidity in defense. So little game left. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: 58' Meram with a beautiful turn. His cross finds Kamara, no Jimenez, no Kamara. GOAL! 3-1 #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: That goal was all set up by Justin Meram’s incredible touch to get past Tyrone Mears. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: David Smith
timelineItems.text: Kei Kamara is a beast. #gocrew #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Two subs in the 62', #Sounders Neagle in, Pappa out, #CrewSC Wahl in, Saeid out.

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Not entirely suprising that #CrewSC continues to blur the line between holding midfielder and center back. Trapp ended up back there too.

timelineItems.name: Greg Benson
timelineItems.text: Bogus yellow card aside, Pogatetz is having one of his best games in a #CrewSC jersey. A dominant display. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Sean Maslin
timelineItems.text: The confidence that both #SoundersFC #CrewSC have on the attack is a welcomed sight. Neither team is pulling punches #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: Columbus in the 5-5-1 formation now. Seriously. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Kei Kamara (Columbus Crew SC) header from the center of the box is close, but misses to the right. Assisted by Justin Meram following a corner kick.
timelineItems.title: MISS: Kei Kamara goes for a hat trick, but heads it wide

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: If my math is correct (I was an English major...it may not be), Kei Kamara is on pace for 26 goals this season. #CrewSC

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Columbus Crew SC 3, Seattle Sounders FC 2. Clint Dempsey (Seattle Sounders FC) right footed shot from very close range to the bottom right corner of the goal.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Clint Dempsey strikes as the Sounders look for a comeback

timelineItems.name: Sean Maslin
timelineItems.text: Dempsey's previous run without the ball was a sight to see. It seems that very few players know how to angle runs in open space #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 75' Clint Dempsey with another goal, and it's 3-2. Not quite sure what happened there, but #CrewSC claimed offside.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 75': Goal for the Sounders. Dempsey with his second goal off a rebound from short distance. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Airkeeper
timelineItems.text: Too bad the stats won't show how absolutely well @Stefan24Frei has been for us. Terrible defense and central midfield today. #EBFG #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.desc: Gonzalo Pineda (Seattle Sounders FC) is shown the yellow card.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Gonzalo Pineda and Kei Kamara go into the book

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 77': Yellow cards handed out for Kamara and Seattle's Pineda. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Dempsey bags his second of the night. @SoundersFC within one of of @ColumbusCrew. 3-2 #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: Setting the Table
timelineItems.text: If Dempsey was active by scoring, then he was WAY offside. #CrewSC #MLS

timelineItems.name: Chad Kunde
timelineItems.text: Yikes. Deuce was definitely offside on that goal. #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Far from over after Dempsey matches Kamara's brace with one of his own. Probably should've been offside though. #CrewSC #CLBvSEA

timelineItems.text: 77' YELLOW CARD Columbus Crew for G. Pineda! #CLBvSEA #MLS http://t.co/fLeFOgnUaz
